463
00:37:36,525 --> 00:37:38,206
This is Hellblade.

464
00:37:38,947 --> 00:37:43,269
In Hellblade, of course, and in many other games, they use preemptive animation.

465
00:37:43,609 --> 00:37:49,253
It gives you well enough time to see when and where the next attack is coming by having

466
00:37:49,273 --> 00:37:51,934
this animation of the enemy.

467
00:37:53,093 --> 00:38:02,165
Also, here's another cool trick to introduce this telegraphy by actually literally saying

468
00:38:02,505 --> 00:38:07,912
